## [11] "XI"   "XII"  "XIII" "XIV"  "XV"   "XVI"  "MT"
yeast_info_renamed <-
  yeast_info |> 
  rename(sequence_name = `Sequence-Name`,
         sequence_length = `Sequence-Length`,
         seqid = `RefSeq-Accn`)
yeast_info_renamed |>
  ggplot(aes(x = sequence_length, 
             y = sequence_name)) +
  geom_col(fill = "white", color='black', width = 0.5) + 
  theme_classic()

yeast_info_renamed |>
  filter(sequence_name != "MT") |>
  ggplot(aes(x = sequence_length, 
             y = as.factor(as.integer(as.roman(sequence_name))))) +
  scale_y_discrete(breaks=1:17, 
                   labels=as.character(as.roman(1:17)),
                   limits = rev) +
  geom_col(fill = "white", color='black', width = 0.5) + 
  theme_classic()

yeast_ftrs <- read_tsv("~/Desktop/saccharomyces_genes_mRNAs_exons.tsv")
## Rows: 19316 Columns: 13
##  Column specification 
## Delimiter: "\t"
## chr (11): seqid, source, type, score, strand, phase, attributes, id, parent,...
## dbl  (2): start, end
## 
##  Use `spec()` to retrieve the full column specification for this data.
##  Specify the column types or set `show_col_types = FALSE` to quiet this message.
names(yeast_ftrs)
##  [1] "seqid"      "source"     "type"       "start"      "end"       
##  [6] "score"      "strand"     "phase"      "attributes" "id"        
## [11] "parent"     "gene_name"  "locus_name"
# Create the 
joined_data <- 
  inner_join(yeast_ftrs, yeast_info_renamed, by="seqid") |>
  mutate(midpoint = (start + end)/2)

yeast_info_renamed |>
  ggplot(aes(x = sequence_length, 
             y = sequence_name)) +
  geom_col(fill = "white", color='black', width = 0.5) +
  geom_point(data = joined_data,
             mapping = aes(x = midpoint, 
                           y = sequence_name),
             size = 0.25,
             alpha = 0.1) + 
  theme_classic()

roi <-
  joined_data |>
  dplyr::filter(type == "gene") |>
  dplyr::filter(sequence_name == "I") |>
  dplyr::filter(start >= 125000, end <= 140000) |>
  dplyr::mutate(orientation = (strand == "+"))

ggplot(roi, aes(xmin = start, 
                xmax = end, 
                y = sequence_name,
                fill = gene_name, 
                forward = orientation)) + 
  geom_gene_arrow()
